{
  "texts": [
    "For example: Rule based technique is challenging to develop a rules for every potential pattern because rule-based techniques are domain-specific as they may not perform in a better way in any other domains.",
    "Machine learning techniques can be computationally expensive which may not be suitable for real-time applications since they are sensitive to the amount of the input and it will need complete normalization or standardization as utilizing a large number of test datasets and the characteristics derived from the documents, machine learning algorithms provide an useful analysis.",
    "For deep learning model, data quality is very much important.",
    "The performance of a model could potentially be affected by noisy or incorrectly classified information and also it can be time consuming as it requires large dataset corpus.",
    "Hybrid methods often provide a balance between rule-based precision and learning-based recall, making them particularly useful in scenarios with diverse linguistic patterns."
  ]
}